    "# Why?\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cybersecurity incidents are growing in frequency and complexity.**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Security teams must communicate threat patterns to management quickly\n",
    "- Raw incident tables are hard to scan and even harder to present\n",
    "- Comparing attack frequency versus attack severity requires manual aggregation\n",
    "- Patterns across country, industry, attack type, and vulnerability are hidden in tabular data\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Today's reality:** Analysts export CSVs, build static charts in Excel, and assemble slide decks manually — for every reporting cycle.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What We Built\n",
    "\n",
    "An **interactive web-based visual report** that makes patterns in 3,000 cybersecurity incidents immediately visible:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Trend overview: how incidents evolved from 2015 to 2024\n",
    "- Country and industry comparisons by frequency *and* severity\n",
    "- Attack type and vulnerability profiles\n",
    "- Defense mechanism outcomes\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "All in a **single Quarto site** — no manual aggregation, published on GitHub Pages.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# For Whom?\n",
    "\n",
    "## Persona 1 — Sophia, Senior Cybersecurity Analyst {.smaller}\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"60%\"}\n",
    "- Age 34, works in a security operations environment\n",
    "- Prepares internal reports and trend analysis regularly\n",
    "- **High** domain expertise and data literacy\n",
    "- Uses a 27\" desktop monitor\n",
    "- Needs analytical depth and cross-category comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "> *\"I need to see which vulnerability types are exploited most in Banking — and whether that's different from Healthcare.\"*\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"40%\"}\n",
    "**Jobs:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Analyse attack trends by year, country, industry\n",
    "- Compare vulnerabilities and defense outcomes\n",
    "- Prepare evidence-based briefings\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pains:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Manually combining static charts is time-consuming\n",
    "- Existing summaries don't support multi-dimensional comparison\n",
    "- Hard to distinguish frequent threats from severe ones\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Persona 2 — Marcus, IT Security Manager {.smaller}\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"60%\"}\n",
    "- Age 48, responsible for security priorities at management level\n",
    "- Communicates risk to senior leadership\n",
    "- **Medium** data literacy, limited time for exploration\n",
    "- Uses a 14\" corporate laptop\n",
    "- Needs a clear entry point and fast time-to-insight\n",
    "\n",
    "> *\"Show me the most affected industries and the biggest financial losses — I need to justify our budget priorities.\"*\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"40%\"}\n",
    "**Jobs:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Get a quick overview of key threat patterns\n",
    "- Identify high-risk sectors and attack types\n",
    "- Communicate findings to executive stakeholders\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pains:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Complex dashboards create friction and reduce trust\n",
    "- Purely technical views don't translate to management communication\n",
    "- Hard to distinguish frequency from severity at a glance\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data Source\n",
    "\n",
    "## Kaggle — Global Cybersecurity Threats (2015–2024)\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"55%\"}\n",
    "**What is it?**\n",
    "\n",
    "A public dataset of 3,000 cybersecurity incidents spanning 2015 to 2024, published on Kaggle (CC0 licence).\n",
    "\n",
    "**What does it cover?**\n",
    "\n",
    "- 10 countries: Australia, Brazil, China, France, Germany, India, Japan, Russia, UK, USA\n",
    "- 7 industries: Banking, Education, Government, Healthcare, IT, Retail, Telecommunications\n",
    "- 10 variables per incident\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"45%\"}\n",
    "**Variable overview:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Variable | Type |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Country, Year | Context |\n",
    "| Attack Type, Attack Source | Threat |\n",
    "| Target Industry, Vulnerability | Target |\n",
    "| Defense Mechanism | Response |\n",
    "| Financial Loss (M$) | Severity |\n",
    "| Affected Users | Severity |\n",
    "| Resolution Time (h) | Severity |\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Data Acquisition\n",
    "\n",
    "**Automated download via `data_acquisition/load.py`:**\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "import kaggle\n",
    "kaggle.api.dataset_download_files(\n",
    "    \"atharvasoundankar/global-cybersecurity-threats-2015-2024\",\n",
    "    path=\"data/raw/\", unzip=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "- Credentials stored in `.env` (never committed)\n",
    "- Any team member can reproduce the acquisition independently\n",
    "- Column names normalised to lowercase snake_case at load time\n",
    "- No missing values — no imputation required\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
